Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_MATCH_STATEMENT handlers (11005)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_MATCH_STATEMENT pre: allocates the merge label and a per-arm
labels array (size = case_count * 3 because each arm needs
check_label, case_label, next_label). The MATCH frame holds these
plus the scrutinee value (filled in child_exit(0)).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. Read case_count at HIR_MATCH_STATEMENT offset 16 (the
   when_clauses list length, but the HIR node also stores the
   count directly at offset 16 in the layout used by the visitor).
2. Allocate merge_label and a 3*case_count*8 byte labels array.
3. For each arm i, pre-allocate three labels and store them at
   offsets i*3*8 + {0,8,16} of the array.
4. Push the MATCH frame.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
case_count * 3 label allocations per match. Cold.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Allocation failures return 0.
@End Security_Scope

