Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_TRY_STATEMENT pre: allocates try/catch/merge labels and reads
the exception type and exception var id directly from the HIR
node. Emits a MIR_INVOKE pseudo-terminator that registers the
catch_label as the unwind destination, then emits the try_label
leader marker.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. Read exception_type at offset 32, exception_var_id at offset
   40.
2. Allocate three labels.
3. Push TRY frame.
4. The current MIR pipeline does not yet have a dedicated invoke-
   for-block helper; we emit a MIR_JUMP(try_label) marker as the
   pseudo-invoke. The full landingpad wiring is set up in
   child_exit(0).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Three label allocations per try.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Defensive null checks.
@End Security_Scope

